article.headline: Pondexter shines as Scarlet Knights extend win streak
article.linkText: Pondexter's career-high 31 helps Rutgers fly past Hoyas
article.story:
WASHINGTON (AP) -- Cappie Pondexter scored a career-high 31
points to lead Rutgers (No. 23 ESPN/USA Today, No. 22 AP) to a 93-52 victory over Georgetown on
Saturday, extending the Scarlet Knights' winning streak to nine
games.

	   Mauri Horton scored 19 points and Dawn McCullough added 13 for
Rutgers (18-5, 11-2 Big East). Chelsea Newton had 10 points and 10
rebounds.

	   Rutgers, which had a season-high point total, last had a
nine-game winning streak from Jan. 30-Feb. 28, 1999.

	   Nok Duany scored 12 points for Georgetown (14-10, 5-8). Rebekkah
Brunson and Mary Lisicky each scored 10. The Hoyas have lost two
straight and four of six.

	   Pondexter scored nine of her 17 first-half points in a
game-opening 15-1 run.

	   The Hoyas missed their first eight shots before Sarah Jenkins
hit a 3-pointer from the left corner with 11:38 left in the first
half.

	   A 3-pointer by Jenkins started a 10-3 run, and Georgetown twice
cut the lead to seven points.

	   But Rutgers quickly regained control, beating the 30-second
clock with long shots four times in the final 3:34.

	   Georgetown made just four shots from the field in the first 7:12
of the second half and trailed 62-30 when Horton finished a 3-on-1
break with a layup with 11:40 remaining.
